# IronPulse compatibility layer

This generated project includes a compact, dependency-light IronPulse-style support layer under
`lib.ironpulse`. It is ordinary Java source owned by the robot project and remains usable without
FRC Framework.

Included building blocks:

- real and simulated TalonFX motor IO, configuration, motion commands, zeroing, and SysId;
- digital, analog, and simulated beam-break IO with logging, debounce, triggers, and wait commands;
- fixed-duration and condition-driven controller rumble commands;
- reusable edge and time-delay boolean utilities.

Preset-specific Swerve and Limelight sources are added only when those presets are selected, so an
empty project stays small and understandable.

## Acknowledgement

The package organization and several API concepts were informed by the library maintained by FRC
Team 6941, IronPulse Robotics (`ironpulse6941`). Thank you to the team for sharing its FRC software
architecture and engineering ideas. FRC Framework's compatibility sources are independently
implemented for this Base; the upstream repository is not bundled wholesale.
